Time-series interpolation types
InstVal = Instantaneous Value, linear interpolation between observations. For example continuous watercourse level.
PrecVal = Preceeding period average value. For example daily avergae flow for the 1st day of Jan 2012 would have timestamp 02/01/2012 00:00
PrecMax = Preceding period maximum value. For example maximum weekly watercourse discharge
PrecMin = Preceding period minimum value. For example daily minimum temperature
PrecTot = Preceding period total value. For example daily total rainfall for the 1st day of Jan 2012 would have date stamp 02/01/2012 00:00
InstTot = Instantaneous total, total value that ocurred at an event
NoJoin  = Discontinuous value, collection occurs infrequently and interpolation or integration not possible
SuccVal = Succeeding period Value, value holds until changed
PrecDir = Preceding period directional value.  For example wind direction
